HEADWORD: Pleurotoma
<hw>Pleu*rot"o*ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> L. <plw>Pleurotom⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E.
<plw>Pleurotomas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ the
side + <grk>tomh`</grk> a cut.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any marine
gastropod belonging to <gen>Pleurotoma</gen>, and ether allied genera of
the family <fam>Pleurotmid⟦ae⟧</fam>. The species are very numerous,
especially in tropical seas. The outer lip has usually a posterior notch
or slit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

